TY  - JOUR
T1  - Turnover: Liquidity or Uncertainty?
AU  - Barinov, Alexander
Y1  - 2014/06/17
PY  - 2014
DA  - 2014/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.2014.1913
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.2014.1913
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 2478
EP  - 2495
VL  - 60
IS  - 10
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - I show that turnover is unrelated to several alternative measures of liquidity risk and in most cases negatively, not positively, related to liquidity. Consequently, neither liquidity nor liquidity risk explains why higher turnover predicts lower future returns. I find that the aggregate volatility risk factor explains why higher turnover predicts lower future returns. This paper shows that the negative relation between turnover and future returns is stronger for firms with option-like equity, and this regularity is also explained by the aggregate volatility risk factor. This paper was accepted by Wei Jiang, finance.
AB  - I show that turnover is unrelated to several alternative measures of liquidity risk and in most cases negatively, not positively, related to liquidity. Consequently, neither liquidity nor liquidity risk explains why higher turnover predicts lower future returns. I find that the aggregate volatility risk factor explains why higher turnover predicts lower future returns. This paper shows that the negative relation between turnover and future returns is stronger for firms with option-like equity, and this regularity is also explained by the aggregate volatility risk factor. This paper was accepted by Wei Jiang, finance.
